<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1070] C++ compiler and runtime have 32/64bit problems</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1070</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When compiling thrift with a 64bit G++ and a strict set of warnings, some errors come up.  The code assumes that sizeof(size_t)==sizeof(int32_t).  Since most of these problems are related to the wire protocol, which defines a four-byte size, the fixes are straightforward casting.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We&apos;ll provide a patch shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
